This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of word alignments, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and the evaluation of the models involves measuring their performance, which is a task in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image captioning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
